*** THE DECISIVE RE-CHECK (HARD RULE 6: re-audit adversarially before claiming a lever) ***
The period 4th moment IS THE ADDITIVE ENERGY. Verified exactly:
   E4(mu_n) := #{(a,b,c,d) in mu_n^4 : a+b = c+d mod p}.  At n=16, p=65617:  E4 = 720,  E4/n^2 = 2.812
   — IDENTICAL to the measured m4_r = 2.810. (sum_b |eta_b|^4 = p*E4 by orthogonality.)
So the real>iid 4th-moment excess (m4_r/m4_i ~ 1.45) is EXACTLY an ADDITIVE-ENERGY excess of mu_n above
the random-set baseline (E4 ~ 2n^2 for a Sidon-like set; mu_n carries the extra multiplicative-coset
additive correlations, E4/n^2 ~ 2.8). This is the standard fact that a multiplicative subgroup has
additive energy above a random set.

VERDICT: the cocycle's residual structure is a MOMENT (additive energy E4), NOT a non-moment lever.
HARD RULE 5 / #444 §6 declares additive-moment/energy bounds PROVEN non-proving (the §3 meta-theorem:
moment/energy estimates are capped at Johnson / saturate at structured primes; door (i) = BGK). So the
+15-44% sup excess is fully explained by mu_n's additive energy, which is exactly the door-(i) moment
quantity that cannot prove CORE. The dispersion-magnitude probe's "real disperses less than iid" is
therefore NOT a new lever — it is the additive energy of the subgroup, re-entering through door (i).

This CLOSES the last door-(iv) Lane-1 sub-hope (that the dispersion EXCESS hides exploitable structure):
the excess is a moment, the moment door is dead, so there is no non-moment signal left in the period field.
Combined with the dispersion-magnitude result (no edge over random) and the two worst-b NOTEs (delocalized
index, extreme-value tail), the door-(iv) Lane-1 object is now characterized from every side and routes
ENTIRELY into the proven-dead doors (i) [moment/energy] + (iii) [extreme-value].

NON-CLAIM: refutation-WITH-mechanism of the "dispersion excess = exploitable non-moment structure" hope.
CORE stays OPEN. No CORE/cancellation/completion/moment-saving/anti-concentration/capacity claim.

